Well, I went back on Friday evening, and after killing many &quot;A Skeletons&quot;, another Paladin waltzed in and announced that he was willing to pay to loot the hilt... He then sent me a tell asking if I knew where the spawn area was. I replied saying I was looking for the hilt also, but did not know the exact drop location, only that it came from &quot;A Skeleton&quot;. He said that he would wait for me to find it first. After a bit, he went off to WK to talk to the guy and get the bag for the quest and told me that his roomate said the two skeletons by the water were the ones that dropped the hilt. After he left I went down to the water area, and after killing just 5 skeletons, there it was, the hilt! <br>
Sooooo, to make a very long winded and boring story just a tiny bit shorter, As most of you now know, I have my Ghoulbane.<br>
I would like to thank all in the guild who helped me with this, specifically those on the raid day itself, by providing transportation (Justims and Nevarmoor), the much appreciated heals (Ceelia and Pyranius), Awsome nukes (Sindiin and Noltrac), a goodly helping of the dark arts (Ischaade and Gwetto), Lovely music (Gwenne), our Najena guide, &quot;Pointer-out-of-traps&quot;, and holder of the &quot;Get out of jail free key&quot; (Sibian), and of course my fellow Paladin, the all around lovely and deadly tank (Branwen).<br>
That wraps up that. I had a blast and hope to be able to help other of our mid level guildmates with their respective quests. If no one posts anything soon however, I may be forced to come up with another one for Radnor, and subject you all to my stories again! <br>
